Marksmanship Hunter Mythic+ Guide

11.0.7 - The War Within

Last Updated:February 3, 2025|Changelog|FAQ

Welcome to the Marksmanship Hunter Mythic+ guide for the World of Warcraft patch 11.0.5! This guide covers everything you need to know to understand your character! Are you starting out and leveling up from 70? Check out the leveling guide!

Hero Talents

Patch 11.0.7 - The War Within
Marksmanship Hunter
  • Your two new Hero Talent trees are
    ‍Dark Ranger     and
    ‍Sentinel    .
  • They both provide defensive benefit in different that are important to your survivability and should be taken into account, with
    ‍Dark Ranger     being more useful defensively in general.
‍Sentinel
‍Dark Ranger
  • The
    ‍Sentinel     hero talent tree mostly provides passive benefits and does not introduce an additional button to your rotation.
  • Mainly revolves around
    ‍Sentinel     applying up to 10 stacks to your target through different means within the hero talent tree which have a chance to activate, removing the stacks and dealing damage to the target.
  • The talent
    ‍Symphonic Arsenal     gives this talent tree significant damage increase in stacked multi-target situations with each
    ‍Multi-Shot     you use.
  • The capstone talent,
    ‍Lunar Storm    , makes it important for you to time a
    ‍Rapid Fire     whenever
    ‍Lunar Storm     is off cooldown to proc this ability on your target and increasing your damage you do to it and enemies around it.
  • ‍Sentinel     grants you
    ‍Don't Look Back    , which is useful if a dungeon has a lot of big hits that you could use extra absorbs for to live.
  • This hero talent tree introduces
    ‍Black Arrow     to replace
    ‍Kill Shot    , changing how it interacts with your gameplay.
    • Usable on enemies below 20% health, above 80% health through
      ‍The Bell Tolls      , and whenever you proc
      ‍Deathblow      .
    • Interacts with
      ‍Trick Shots       through
      ‍Bleak Powder      , giving it more AoE potential.
    • Many talents in the
      ‍Dark Ranger       tree like
      ‍Shadow Surge      ,
      ‍Banshee's Mark       and
      ‍Phantom Pain       all incentivizes you to always use your
      ‍Black Arrow       on different targets, spreading out the DoT effect and increasing its effectiveness.
    • Is shot out automatically during your
      ‍Trueshot       window through the talent
      ‍Withering Fire      .
  • ‍Bleak Arrows     increases the value of your auto shots, giving you a chance to proc
    ‍Deathblow    .
  • ‍Dark Ranger     applies
    ‍Survival of the Fittest     to you when you use
    ‍Exhilaration     through the talent
    ‍Smoke Screen    , making it an on demand damage reduction cooldown.
  • Using
    ‍Survival of the Fittest     with this talent chosen also heals you for 50% of what a normal
    ‍Exhilaration     would.
    • Shares choice node with
      ‍Embrace the Shadows      . About 30% of your damage is shadow damage as a
      ‍Dark Ranger       so this provides a decent chunk of healing to yourself.

Talents

Patch 11.0.7 - The War Within
Marksmanship Hunter
‍Sentinel Mythic+ Talents

When to use this Spec

Use this spec on all key levels.

Gameplay Altering Talents

Discover all talents that significantly alter your gameplay within the Spec and Class Talent trees. This section gives a concise overview of these talents and their applications but for a more detailed look check out the Rotation and Deep Dive sections below.

Spec Tree

  • ‍Rapid Fire     +
    ‍Aimed Shot
    • Your core damage dealing abilities as a Marksmanship Hunter. They are buffed by a lot of other talents you pick throughout your Talent Tree.
  • ‍Multi-Shot     +
    ‍Trick Shots     +
    ‍Volley
    • Enables your entire AoE damage dealing kit. This combo is used in all 3+ target scenarios.
  • ‍Careful Aim     +
    ‍Bullseye
    • Focuses a lot of your damage dealing potential on targets above 70% health and below 20% health.
  • ‍Lone Wolf
    • Incentivizes you to play without a Pet active.
  • ‍Steady Focus
    • Takes an otherwise very low priority ability,
      ‍Steady Shot      , and gives it a lot more purpose in your rotation.
  • ‍Deathblow
    • Enables
      ‍Kill Shot      /
      ‍Black Arrow       usage in your rotation over the entire duration of a fight, as opposed to its usual use on targets below 20% health.
  • ‍Wailing Arrow
    • Transforms
      ‍Aimed Shot       after gaining 20 stacks of Wind Arrows through
      ‍Legacy of the Windrunners      , giving it additional effects.
  • ‍Trueshot
    • You main offensive cooldown, enhanced by multiple talents after it to make it a very important part of your kit.

Class Tree

  • ‍Padded Armor
    • Grants
      ‍Survival of the Fittest       two charges this and
      ‍Lone Survivor       make up for a majority of your Defensive capabilities.
  • ‍Natural Mending
    • Heavily reduces the cooldown of your
      ‍Exhilaration       ability, allowing you to heal yourself on demand quite often.
  • ‍Emergency Salve
    • Grants
      ‍Feign Death       and
      ‍Aspect of the Turtle       the capability to dispel you on fights that apply Poison or Disease debuffs to you. Occasionally extremely useful to help yourself and your group.

Hero Talents

  • ‍Sentinel Watch
    • Generally more value for the Cooldown Reduction it provides compared to increased burst window damage with
      ‍Eyes Closed      .
  • ‍Overwatch
    • Overall more value in keys, although
      ‍Crescent Steel       can be good for bosses/minibosses.
  • ‍Sideline
    • Always picked since
      ‍Catch Out       can cause issues with its random roots.

Rotation

Patch 11.0.7 - The War Within
Marksmanship Hunter

Tier Set

  • 2-Set:
    ‍Arcane Shot     and
    ‍Multi-Shot     damage increased by 20%.
  • 4-Set: Consuming
    ‍Precise Shot     increases the damage of your next
    ‍Aimed Shot     by 20%.

Single-Target

‍Sentinel

Opener

  • Your goal in the opener is simply to use as many
    ‍Rapid Fires     and
    ‍Aimed Shots     as possible, while filling in with
    ‍Arcane Shot     if both are on cooldown.
  • Always apply
    ‍Hunter's Mark     on the boss before combat.
  • Always be on the lookout for cooldown resets on
    ‍Rapid Fires     and
    ‍Aimed Shots     during your cooldowns to quickly change your priority for increased damage.
  • If you're using
    ‍Treacherous Transmitter     it has a "puzzle" you need to solve to gain the effect, use it 10~ seconds before you use your
    ‍Trueshot     and identify and delay solving the puzzle until then.
    This puts the trinket on cooldown earlier and allows for differently timed uses later on to line up with
    ‍Trueshot     again.
    • If you use the recommended trinket
      ‍Skardyn's Grace       or any other normal on use trinket, use them with your
      ‍Trueshot      .
  • Use
    ‍Tempered Potion     and racials like
    ‍Blood Fury     or
    ‍Berserking     right as you use your
    ‍Trueshot    .

Priority List

This is a general priority you aim to maintain throughout the fight.

  1. If
    ‍Trueshot     is NOT active and
    ‍Steady Focus     is not up, proc it by using
    ‍Steady Shot    .
  2. Use
    ‍Explosive Shot     on cooldown.
  3. Use
    ‍Salvo     on cooldown.
  4. Place
    ‍Volley     on your targets to activate
    ‍Trick Shots    .
  5. Cast
    ‍Rapid Fire     on cooldown.
  6. Cast
    ‍Aimed Shot     if you're at or close to having 2 charges.
  7. Use
    ‍Kill Shot     if your target is under 20% health.
  8. Use
    ‍Arcane Shot    .
  9. Cast the rest of your
    ‍Aimed Shot    .
  10. Cast
    ‍Steady Shot     if you're too low on Focus and everything above is on cooldown.

AoE

‍Sentinel

Opener

  • Your goal in the AoE opener is to use as many
    ‍Rapid Fires     and
    ‍Aimed Shots     with
    ‍Trick Shots     active as possible.
  • Always apply
    ‍Hunter's Mark     on the highest health mob before combat.
  • At the start of the opener you have
    ‍Volley     activating
    ‍Trick Shots     for you, but once it runs out you need to start using
    ‍Multi-Shot     in between each
    ‍Rapid Fires     and
    ‍Aimed Shots     you cast to make sure they cleave their damage.
  • If you're using
    ‍Treacherous Transmitter     it has a "puzzle" you need to solve to gain the effect, use it 10~ seconds before you use your
    ‍Trueshot     and identify and delay solving the puzzle until then.
    This puts the trinket on cooldown earlier and allows for differently timed uses later on to line up with
    ‍Trueshot     again.
    • If you use the recommended trinket
      ‍Skardyn's Grace       or any other normal on use trinket, use them with your
      ‍Trueshot      .
  • Use
    ‍Tempered Potion     and racials like
    ‍Blood Fury     or
    ‍Berserking     right as you use your
    ‍Trueshot    .

Priority List

  1. If
    ‍Trueshot     is NOT active and
    ‍Steady Focus     is not up, proc it by using
    ‍Steady Shot    .
  2. Use
    ‍Explosive Shot     on cooldown.
  3. Use
    ‍Salvo     on cooldown.
  4. Place
    ‍Volley     on your targets to activate
    ‍Trick Shots    .
  5. Use
    ‍Multi-Shot     to activate
    ‍Trick Shots     if it is NOT currently active.
  6. Cast
    ‍Rapid Fire     on cooldown.
  7. Cast
    ‍Aimed Shot     on cooldown.
  8. Use
    ‍Kill Shot     if your target is under 20% health.
  9. Use
    ‍Multi-Shot     if nothing else is available.
  10. Cast
    ‍Steady Shot     if you're too low on Focus and everything above is on cooldown.

Deep Dive

Patch 11.0.7 - The War Within
Marksmanship Hunter

The Importance of
‍Trick Shots on AoE

  • It is crucial for you to ALWAYS have the
    ‍Trick Shots     buff active before you use
    ‍Rapid Fire     or
    ‍Aimed Shot     in AoE scenarios no matter what.
  • Remember that using either of them always consumes your current
    ‍Trick Shots     buff, except when you have
    ‍Volley     running which constantly applies
    ‍Trick Shots     while active.
  • Not doing this in all AoE cases results in a significant loss of overall damage.

Maximizing your
‍Trueshot uses

  • ‍Trueshot     has a baseline cooldown of 2 minutes, but with the talent
    ‍Calling the Shots     you reduce it to about 1:20-1:30~ seconds (even lower with
    ‍Sentinel Watch    ) depending on how much Focus you spend, your uptime and your Haste.
    • Always try to use it again as soon as possible after it comes up, since you lose out on cooldown reduction for your next
      ‍Trueshot       if you don't, decreasing the number of uses you get over the duration of the dungeon.
    • However, you don't want to use your
      ‍Trueshot       in a way that leaves it active while you're in between pulls and not doing damage to anything. If a pull is close to dying when
      ‍Trueshot       comes off cooldown you should still hold it for the next pull instead.

Potentially good Talent Swaps you can make

There are a few talents in the default build that are situationally not very useful that you need to keep in mind.

  • Swapping away from talents like
    ‍Emergency Salve     if there is no Poison or Disease dispel in the dungeon or
    ‍Camouflage     if you don't find stealth useful for the current dungeon.
    • Good replacements if you decide to do this are
      ‍Kodo Tranquilizer       or
      ‍Devilsaur Tranquilizer       if you need more Magic or Enrage dispels.
    • ‍Bursting Shot       if you find yourself in need of more stops or another knockback.
    • ‍Moment of Opportunity       to get a burst of movement speed increase when a Trap that you placed is triggered.
    • ‍Ghillie Suit       can be useful on certain trash, giving you an extra defensive cooldown by using
      ‍Feign Death       +
      ‍Camouflage       in quick succession.
    • ‍Binding Shackles       if you don't find any use for either of the aforementioned talents.
    • You can always swap from
      ‍Implosive Trap       to
      ‍High Explosive Trap       if you ever need to push the mobs away rather than keeping them in place.

Rotational min-maxing is just one aspect of mastering a specialization, but there are numerous other key mechanics that influence your performance. Use the following guides to improve them.

Boss Tips

Avanoxx

  • Use defensives on
    ‍Alerting Shrill    .
  • Avoid kiting Starved Crawlers into the boss else the boss receives
    ‍Insatiable    .
    • Use
      ‍Tar Trap       and
      ‍Binding Shot       to keep them slowed and more stacked.
    • AoE them down as soon as possible, ignoring the boss while they're up.
  • Try to move together as a team to bait
    ‍Gossamer Onslaught     webs on the ground in the same place, leaving you more space to control the adds.

Anub'zekt

  • Watch where your tank is facing the boss to avoid
    ‍Impale    , especially during
    ‍Eye of the Swarm    .
  • Kill Bloodstained Webmages fast and interrupt
    ‍Silken Restraints    .
  • Use a defensive on
    ‍Infestation     and avoid all
    ‍Ceaseless Swarm     in the room.

Ki'katal the Harvester

  • Play spread from the group on this boss, and whenever
    ‍Cultivated Poisons     is cast you can
    ‍Feign Death     to dispel yourself.
  • Help with hitting any Bloodworkers if necessary to spawn
    ‍Grasping Blood    .
  • When you're affected by
    ‍Grasping Blood     you can disengage to break free from the root after
    ‍Cosmic Singularity     finished its cast.
    • You can also use any of your CCs on the adds on other players to break them free from their roots.

Trash Tips

  • Important abilities to interrupt in this dungeon are:
    • ‍Resonant Barrage       from Trilling Attendant.
    • ‍Horrifying Shrill       from Ixin.
    • ‍Revolting Volley       from Bloodstained Webmage.
    • ‍Venom Volley       from Blood Overseer.
  • Pay extra attention to these casts:
    • ‍Alarm Shrill       from Sentry Stagshell
      • A really long cast that needs to get disrupted.
    • ‍Massive Slam       from Nerubian Hauler and Hulking Bloodguard
      • A short stun that ramps in damage done per cast.
  • Use a defensive for
    ‍Call of the Brood     while fighting Nakt.

Pre Dungeon Start

  • Use
    ‍Tempered Potion     just before the key is activated to increase your damage on the first pull.

Boss Tips

Orator Krix'vizk

  • ‍Chains of Oppression     keeps you from playing in ranged on this boss.
  • When you have
    ‍Shadows of Doubt     on you, try to stay on the edge of the circle to make it easier for everyone to dodge the orbs.
  • Use your defensives during
    ‍Vociferous Indoctrination     and be ready to move out of the damage zone that spawns under the boss.
  • Dodge
    ‍Terrorize     whenever it is cast.

Fangs of the Queen

  • Watch out for
    ‍Knife Throw    . Use a defensive if you're targeted by this ability.
  • Spread from other teammates whenever Vx casts
    ‍Ice Sickles    , and
    ‍Disengage     after the damage debuff is applied to you to remove it.
  • Whenever Vx uses
    ‍Rime Dagger     on the tank, walk in to the circle around your tank to help remove stacks of the debuff.
  • Multiple
    ‍Echoing Shade     spawn throughout the fight that mimic Nx's
    ‍Shade Slash     frontal and
    ‍Duskbringer     circle, so keep an eye out for where they're spawned.

The Coaglamation

  • Use a defensive for each
    ‍Dark Pulse    . This happens at 100 boss energy.
  • Whenever the boss casts
    ‍Viscous Darkness    , position yourself so you don't get knocked into any pools on the ground and soak any orbs that are moving towards the boss.

Izo, the Grand Splicer

  • At the start of the fight Izo spawns orbs. Throughout the fight these orbs launch at a player in the group, make sure you dodge them and don't stand in the line they're travelling.
  • Mainly use your defensives for
    ‍Splice     since it's the highest damage event during this fight and only use leftover defensives for the
    ‍Tremor Slam    .
  • Kill off the Ravenous Scarabs as they spawn and use
    ‍Binding Shot     and
    ‍Tar Trap     to help control them.
  • For the
    ‍Umbral Weave     you use
    ‍Disengage     to free yourself from the root. After that, help kill any other webs remaining to free other players.
  • Avoid the circle around the tank when the boss casts
    ‍Process of Elimination    .

Trash Tips

  • Important abilities to interrupt in this dungeon are:
    • ‍Web Bolt       from Sureki Silkbinder.
    • ‍Grimweave Blast       from Covert Webmancer.
    • ‍Mending Web       from Covert Webmancer.
    • ‍Twist Thoughts       from Herald of Anurek.
    • ‍Void Wave       from Sureki Unnaturaler.
  • While fighting Xeph'itik, use a defensive if targeted by
    ‍Perfume Toss    .
  • Use a defensive when affected by
    ‍Void Rush     while fighting Eye of the Queen.
  • If the Royal Venomshell applies
    ‍Venomous Spray     to you, use
    ‍Feign Death     to dispel it with
    ‍Emergency Salve    .
  • When fighting the Elder Shadeweaver make sure you damage her absorb shield quickly to allow interrupting again.
    • When she casts
      ‍Umbral Weave      , use
      ‍Disengage       to break free and kill any remaining webs to help other players.
  • When the Hulking Warshell casts
    ‍Tremor Slam    , sse a defensive right before this cast finishes.
    • Kill off the Ravenous Scarabs quickly when they spawn. You can place a
      ‍Binding Shot       and
      ‍Tar Trap       to control them better.

Boss Tips

E.D.N.A.

  • Always stack up before
    ‍Volatile Spikes     to spawn them close together to ensure you can break them all with one
    ‍Refracting Beam    .
    • Use a defensive whenever you break the
      ‍Volatile Spikes      .
  • Make sure you don't overlap your
    ‍Refracting Beam     with someone elses.
  • Also keep a defensive for each
    ‍Earth Shatterer    .

Skarmorak

  • Always focus down one Crystal Shard at a time when they are up, and wait for
    ‍Crystalline Eruption     to run out before you kill the next one.
  • Use your defensive before
    ‍Unstable Crash     happens or while you have multiple stacks of
    ‍Unstable Energy     from picking up the orbs.

Master Machinists Brokk and Dorlita

  • Make sure you always keep your interrupt for
    ‍Molten Metal     whenever Speaker Brokk casts it while being far away from the group because of
    ‍Scrap Song    .
  • Stay clear of the middle to avoid
    ‍Scrap Cube     from hitting you.
  • Quickly identify which Exhaust Vent is safe whenever it is cast and stay there until it ends.
  • Always keep an eye out for when Speaker Dorlita casts
    ‍Lava Cannon     to dodge it.
  • Use your defensive during
    ‍Exhaust Vents     and
    ‍Blazing Crescendo    .
  • Make sure you kill both bosses at the same time to avoid
    ‍Silenced Speaker     from being up for too long.

Void Speaker Eirich

  • Whenever you get
    ‍Void Corruption    , quickly move to a portal to remove the debuff before it starts dealing too much damage.
  • Place
    ‍Entropic Reckoning     well so it doesn't disrupt your or anyone else's gameplay and quickly move out of the
    ‍Entropy     pool afterwards.
  • Use a defensive on each
    ‍Entropic Reckoning    .

Trash Tips

  • Focus down
    ‍Earth Burst Totem     from Cursedforge Stoneshaper. They have a low amount of health but are not affected by AoE abilities.
  • Important abilities to interrupt in this dungeon are:
    • ‍Howling Fear       from Ghastly Voidsoul.
    • ‍Censoring Gear       from Turned Speaker.
    • ‍Piercing Wail       from Void Bound Howler.
    • ‍Restoring Metals       from Forgebound Mender and Cursedforge Mender.
    • ‍Arcing Void       from Cursedheart Invader.
  • You can line of sight the
    ‍Ground Pound     cast by Earth Infused Golems.
  • Forge Loaders cast
    ‍Lava Cannon     towards a player that needs to be dodged.
  • Use a defensive whenever you fight Void Bound Despoilers when they cast the ability
    ‍Void Outburst    .
  • When you fight a Rock Smasher mob, use a defensive for each
    ‍Smash Rock     cast.

Pre Dungeon Start

  • Use
    ‍Tempered Potion     just before the key is activated to increase your damage on the first pull.

Boss Tips

Speaker Shadowcrown

  • Pre-position away from the boss before
    ‍Collapsing Night     is cast to spawn the void zone in a good place. Quickly move out of the zone that spawns by using
    ‍Disengage     to reduce damage.
    • Use a defensive every time this is cast on you.
  • Position in a good place for each
    ‍Obsidian Beam     to minimize movement while dodging the beams.
  • Interrupt
    ‍Shadow Bolts     whenever you can.

Anub'ikkaj

  • Position well to aim
    ‍Dark Orb     down an open path, dodge the orb when it shoots out and use a defensive when it is about to explode.
  • Use a defensive for
    ‍Shadowy Decay    .
  • Stay away from the tank to avoid
    ‍Terrifying Slam    .
  • When the boss casts
    ‍Animate Shadows     it spawns Adds, use
    ‍Misdirect     on your tank and AoE them down quickly.
    • Place
      ‍Implosive Trap       on them to stop their casts.

Rasha'nan

  • Make sure you pick up and throw any
    ‍Arathi Bombs     on the boss.
  • When you get
    ‍Rolling Acid    , look at which direction it is going and move out towards that same direction.
  • Be aware of
    ‍Erosive Spray    . It applies
    ‍Lingering Erosion     which is dangerous when combined with other damage events.
  • During Phase 2 the boss starts using
    ‍Spinneret's Strands    . If this is on you, move out of the group, use a defensive and quickly move out of the web that spawns when it runs out.

Trash Tips

  • Important abilities to interrupt in this dungeon are:
    • ‍Night Bolt       from Nightfall Shadowmage.
    • ‍Ensnaring Shadows       from Nightfall Shadowmage.
    • ‍Tormenting Beam       from Nightfall Darkcaster.
    • ‍Umbral Barrier       from Nightfall Darkcaster.
  • When fighting the miniboss Ixkreten the Unbreakable, stay away from where the tank is positioned to not get hit by
    ‍Terrifying Slam    .
  • The second miniboss Deathscreamer Iken'tak casts
    ‍Dark Orb     towards a random player. If this is aimed at you, make sure it's aimed down a long open path to not explode too close to the group, and dodge the orb when it gets shot out.
    • Always use a defensive when
      ‍Dark Orb       is about to explode.
  • On the third miniboss, Ascendant Vis'coxria, use a defensive whenever it casts
    ‍Shadowy Decay    .
  • Right before the last boss you play a miniboss called Nightfall Dark Architect. As this mob dies the boss spawns right after, so make sure you don't body pull the boss and don't have any abilities placed on the ground like traps and
    ‍Volley    .

Pre Dungeon Start

  • Use
    ‍Tempered Potion     just before the key is activated to increase your damage on the first pull.

Boss Tips

Ingra Maloch

  • Interrupt
    ‍Spirit Bolt     every time a non-tank player is targeted.
  • Try to line up your cooldowns with Droman Oulfarran's
    ‍Droman's Wrath     to increase your cooldown's damage significantly. This happens when Droman Oulfarran reaches 20% health.
  • If you have
    ‍Aspect of the Turtle     ready, use it when the boss casts
    ‍Repulsive Visage    .
  • If Ingra Maloch is at low health after a damage increase phase it is more worth it to kill him off rather than pushing for another damage phase.

Mistcaller

  • Use
    ‍Freezing Trap     or
    ‍Binding Shot     on the Illusionary Vulpins to prevent them from reaching their target.
    • If your group is not crowd-controlling the Illusionary Vulpins, kill them off quickly.
  • Use your defensives during the
    ‍Guessing Game    .

Tred'ova

  • When the boss casts
    ‍Acid Expulsion    , don't move too much since all upcoming casts remember your movement from the past ones, sending out extra projectiles to dodge.
  • Use
    ‍Binding Shot     and
    ‍Tar Trap     to control the Gormling Larvas.
  • Stay away from the tank when the boss casts
    ‍Mind Link     to break your tether instantly.

Trash Tips

  • Important abilities to interrupt in this dungeon are:
    • ‍Spirit Bolt       from Drust Harvester.
    • ‍Harvest Essence       from Drust Harvester.
    • ‍Nourish the Forest       from Mistveil Tender.
    • ‍Bramblethorn Coat       from Mistveil Shaper.
    • ‍Stimulate Regeneration       from Spinemaw Staghorn.
    • ‍Stimulate Resistance       from Spinemaw Staghorn.
  • When the Tirnenn Villager casts
    ‍Overgrowth     on you, use
    ‍Feign Death     before it goes through.
  • In the Maze area after the first boss it is usually the healer who solves the puzzle while you kill the trash, but you can help out by standing near one of the symbols for the healer - or solve it yourself if you feel confident and no one else is doing it!
  • At certain points in the Maze area you can summon a pet and send it through the walls to pull more mobs to you.
    • Communicate with your group before you do this since it is difficult to handle if they're not prepared.

Pre Dungeon Start

  • Use
    ‍Tempered Potion     just before the key is activated to increase your damage on the first pull.

Boss Tips

Blightbone

  • Use a defensive if you're targeted by
    ‍Heaving Retch     and stand away from your teammates, ideally towards already placed
    ‍Fetid Gas     on the ground.
    • You can also dispel the Disease effect after you get hit by using
      ‍Feign Death      .
  • Always use
    ‍Tar Trap     and
    ‍Binding Shot     when Carrion Worms spawn, don't let them hit you and cleave them down.

Amarth, The Harvester

  • Use a
    ‍Freezing Trap     on either the Reanimated Crossbowman or Reanimated Mage when the boss spawns adds.
  • If any adds are still alive during
    ‍Final Harvest    , use
    ‍Intimidation     to crowd-control them. With them crowd-controlled, the boss doesn't cast
    ‍Tortured Echoes     even though an add is alive.
    • Stay away from any corpses of adds that have died when the
      ‍Final Harvest       cast finishes.
  • Help interrupt
    ‍Necrotic Bolts     from the boss or
    ‍Frostbolt Volley     from Reanimated Mages.
  • You can help getting the Reanimated Crossbowman closer to the boss for easier cleave by knocking them with
    ‍High Explosive Trap    .

Surgeon Stitchflesh

  • Be in position near Surgeon Stitchflesh's platform throughout the fight to hook him down if you get
    ‍Meat Hooks     targeted on you.
    • When Surgeon Stitchflesh is about to use
      ‍Escape      , make sure you're already in position to hook him down since they often overlap in timing.
  • Make sure you dodge
    ‍Embalming Ichor    .
  • Use
    ‍Feign Death     if you get targeted by
    ‍Morbid Fixation     to interrupt it.
    • This ability can also be stopped by aiming
      ‍Meat Hooks       at the Stitchflesh's Creation.

Nalthor the Rimebinder

  • Stay away from the group at all times and use
    ‍Disengage     to remove
    ‍Frozen Binds     when it's cast on you.
  • If you have a Warlock or Evoker in your group, ask them to set up a
    ‍Demonic Gateway     or use
    ‍Rescue     on you right before you get hit by the
    ‍Dark Exile     projectile.
    • Do note that you still die after 50 seconds after doing this. It's a gain if the boss has low health or the targeted player could struggle in the extra phase.
    • Don't do it if you have 0 combat resurrections ready!
  • If you do get sent down by
    ‍Dark Exile    , make sure you have
    ‍Aspect of the Cheetah     ready to complete the gauntlet quickly.

Trash Tips

  • Important abilities to interrupt in this dungeon are:
    • ‍Drain Fluids       from Corpse Harvester and Corpse Collector.
    • ‍Necrotic Bolt       from Zolramus Sorceror & Zolarmus Necromancer.
    • ‍Rasping Scream       from Skeletal Marauder.
    • ‍Frostbolt Volley       from Reanimted Mage.
    • ‍Goresplatter       from Corpse Collector.
    • ‍Repair Flesh       from Flesh Crafter.
  • When fighting against a Zolramus Necromancer, make sure you focus single-target on that mob instead of cleaving since all the summoned skeletal mobs die either way when he does. No padding allowed!
  • When you play against the two Separation Assistants, make sure to be in position to aim the
    ‍Throw Cleaver     at the mob that is not casting on you.
    • If you get
      ‍Morbid Fixation      , use
      ‍Feign Death      .
  • The last trash mob in the Necropolis, Rotspew, has a damage dealing aura around him that persists even after he dies. Make sure your group doesn't kill him where you want to fight Surgeon Stitchflesh.

Pre Dungeon Start

  • Use
    ‍Tempered Potion     just before the key is activated to increase your damage on the first pull.

Boss Tips

Chopper Redhook

  • Try to line up your cooldowns with the boss walking over Bombs which applies
    ‍Heavy Ordnance     to the boss.
  • Use your movement abilities to help you kite the boss into Bombs if you're fixated.
  • Using
    ‍Freezing Trap     on a newly spawned mob, especially later in the fight, might allow you to ignore it completely. Otherwise always swap to the Irontide Powdershot mobs as they spawn.

Dread Captain Lockwood

  • Focus down the Ashvane Cannoneer during the add phase to quickly use
    ‍Unstable Ordnance     to get the boss down from the ship.
  • During
    ‍Mass Bombardment    , you don't need to dodge the circles instantly as they spawn since they have a few seconds until they explode. Use this to minimize space used and maximize uptime doing damage.
  • Don't stand in front of the boss to avoid
    ‍Clear the Deck    .
  • Use defensives for
    ‍Shoot     and
    ‍Fiery Ricochet    .
  • If your group is lacking slows, placing
    ‍Tar Trap     under the boss helps keep her in place. You can also
    ‍Wing Clip     if absolutely necessary but should be avoided at almost any cost, make someone else do it!

Hadal Darkfathom

  • If you find yourself struggling with positioning for a
    ‍Tidal Surge     combo you can use
    ‍Aspect of the Turtle     to walk through that set of waves.
  • Overall positioning is important here. Make sure to NOT stand near the middle statue except when
    ‍Tidal Surge     is about to come, as to not spawn any Pools from
    ‍Break Water     around that area.

Viq'Goth

  • Focus the Demolishing Terror add first in each phase.
  • You're a decent class for staying and taking care of shooting the Cannon in each phase so consider doing this if your healer or someone else isn't.

Trash Tips

  • Important abilities to interrupt in this dungeon are:
    • ‍Brackish Bolt       from Irontide Waveshaper.
    • ‍Watertight Shell       from Irontide Waveshaper.
    • ‍Water Bolt       from Bilge Rat Tempest.
    • ‍Choking Waters       from Bilge Rat Tempest.
    • ‍Bolstering Shout       from Ashvane Commander.
    • ‍Stinky Vomit       from Bilge Rat Pillager.

Pre Dungeon Start

  • If you are not doing an Invis skip at the start, use
    ‍Tempered Potion     just before the key is activated to increase your damage on the first pull..

Boss Tips

General Umbriss

  • Try to stand around the middle of the room to help you dodge
    ‍Shadowflame Breaths     and save
    ‍Disengage     and
    ‍Aspect of the Cheetah     for this.
  • Use a defensive before each
    ‍Commanding Roar    .
  • Spread on the sides of the room with
    ‍Rock Spike    . When the debuff expires you get knocked in the direction you are facing.

Forgemaster Throngus

  • Whenever the boss uses
    ‍Forge Weapon     he also causes
    ‍Blistering Heat    , use a defensive for each time this happens.
  • Bait
    ‍Fiery Cleave     towards a close wall to increase space.
  • Place
    ‍Molten Sparks     on the sides.

Drahga Shadowburner

  • Whenever the boss casts
    ‍Invocation of Shadowflame    , swap your focus to the Invoked Shadowflame and kill it as soon as possible and use any CC on it if necessary. These adds are not allowed to reach the fixated player.
  • Be careful of the knockback from
    ‍Twilight Buffet     and dodge the
    ‍Tornados     that spawn after.
  • Watch where the tank aims the frontal
    ‍Devouring Flame    .
  • Use a defensive for each
    ‍Twilight Buffet     hit.

Erudax, the Duke of Below

  • Use defensives during
    ‍Abyssal Corruption     and
    ‍Void Surge    .
  • Waiting with killing off any of the Mutated Hatchlings adds until just after
    ‍Void Surge     is cast.
  • When the boss casts
    ‍Shadow Gale    , get to the safe zone and spread out within it for
    ‍Abyssal Corruption     as to not overlap with other players.
    • If you have
      ‍Aspect of the Turtle       available, use it before the
      ‍Abyssal Corruption       cast goes through to most likely avoid it entirely.
  • Dodge Void Tendrils landing on the ground after the boss casts
    ‍Void Surge    .

Trash Tips

  • Important abilities to interrupt in this dungeon are:
    • ‍Earth Bolt       from Twilight Earthcaller.
    • ‍Mass Tremor       from Twilight Earthcaller.
    • ‍Shadowflame Bolt       from Twilight Beguiler.
    • ‍Sear Mind       from Twilight Beguiler.
  • You can line of sight
    ‍Umbral Wind     cast by the Twilight Destroyer.
  • Use a defensive when the Molten Giants cast
    ‍Molten Wake    .
  • Whenever a Twilight Lavabender finishes the cast
    ‍Ascension    , use a defensive a few seconds after to negate some of the damage from
    ‍Scorching Heat    .
  • If a cast of
    ‍Enveloping Shadowflame     goes through on you, use
    ‍Exhilaration     to help heal it off.
  • Near the end of the dungeon you face Faceless Corruptors that cast
    ‍Corrupt    . If this goes on you, use
    ‍Feign Death     to stop its cast if available, or a defensive if not.

Affixes

The Affix system got revamped going into The War Within Season 1 retiring most Affixes as well as introducing new kiss-curse ones while also changing on which key level these appear.

  • +2 Affixes -- Rotates on a weekly basis
    • ‍Xal'atath's Bargain: Ascendant
    • ‍Xal'atath's Bargain: Voidbound
    • ‍Xal'atath's Bargain: Oblivion
    • ‍Xal'atath's Bargain: Devour
  • +4 Affixes -- Alternates between each other on a weekly basis
    • ‍Tyrannical
    • ‍Fortified
  • +7 Affix
    • ‍Challenger's Peril
  • +10 Affixes -- Alternates between each other on a weekly basis, is always the opposite of the +4 Affix
    • ‍Tyrannical
    • ‍Fortified
  • +12 Affix
    • ‍Xal'atath's Guile       -- Replaces the +2 Affix

Below you get some useful tips for handling different Mythic+ Affixes as a Marksmanship Hunter.

  • ‍Xal'atath's Bargain: Ascendant
    • Your strongest tools to deal with these spawns are
      ‍Implosive Trap       and
      ‍Tranquilizing Shot       with
      ‍Kodo Tranquilizer       talented, so make sure you swap to that talent for Ascendant weeks.
  • ‍Xal'atath's Bargain: Voidbound
    • The talent
      ‍Bullseye       get extra value on Voidbound weeks since the spawn starts at low hp.
    • Make sure you swap to it right away, ideally with a
      ‍Rapid Fire       if ready, to gain a lot of Crit from this affix.
  • ‍Xal'atath's Bargain: Oblivion
    • During Oblivion weeks, make sure you play closer to melee in general to intercept these orbs. Both Mastery and Leech are very helpful stats for you so prioritize this over fully minmaxing your damage when they spawn.
  • ‍Xal'atath's Bargain: Devour
    • Your best tool to deal with Devour weeks is
      ‍Emergency Salve       which becomes mandatory in every dungeon. Simply use
      ‍Feign Death       every time this affix is activated to deal with your own debuff instantly.

Stat Priority

Marksmanship Hunter

Understand your secondary stat priority and the tertiary stats needed for optimal performance during Mythic+ dungeons as a Marksmanship Hunter. For more detailed information, visit the Stats and Attributes guide.

Higher Item level items are better in most scenarios. For an accurate representation of what item to equip you should use Simcraft! A static "Stat Priority" is just a starting point and can easily shift depending on your individual gear.

All secondary stats are affected by diminishing returns. Click here to learn more!

Tertiary

  • Avoidance - Great stat to reduce the damage intake of "Area of Effect" abilities.
  • Leech - Provides additional healing through dealing damage. Great stat especially in AoE scenarios.
  • Speed - Way less useful for you since Marksmanship Hunter already has great mobility, but it can help you deal with certain mechanics on bosses, increase your DPS slightly during heavier movement or just help you move through the dungeon quicker.

Races

Patch 11.0.7 - The War Within
Marksmanship Hunter

For min-maxing a Marksmanship Hunter in Mythic+, different racial traits can provide a tremendous benefit to your character. If this is not your top goal, picking a race that fits your style works just as well.

Alliance

  • ‍Stoneform     -- Dwarf
    • Able to dispel a lot of debuffs from you on demand, while also providing you with a 10% physical damage reduction upon use.
  • ‍Might of the Mountain     -- Dwarf
    • Passively increasing your Critical Damage and Healing done by 2%.
  • ‍Will to Survive     -- Human
    • Can break you out of certain CC, even in PvE scenarios.
  • ‍The Human Spirit     -- Human
    • You gain 2% more secondary stats from all sources.
  • ‍Spatial Rift     -- Void Elf
    • Throws out a shadowy projectile in front of you, if you press this button again after the projectile is thrown out, you teleport to its current location. Occasionally extremely helpful for movement.
  • ‍Entropic Embrace     -- Void Elf
    • Occasionally empowering you to deal 5% more damage with all your spells for 12 seconds.

Horde

  • ‍War Stomp     -- Tauren
    • Stuns 5 enemies close to you for 2 seconds.
  • ‍Endurance     -- Tauren
    • Increases your maximum health.
  • ‍Brawn     -- Tauren
    • Passively increasing your Critical Damage and Healing done by 2%.
  • ‍Berserking     -- Troll
    • Increases your Haste by 10% for 12 seconds. Useful if you want a damage racial that provides more burst damage.
  • ‍Rocket Jump     -- Goblin
    • About the same as
      ‍Disengage      , except it launches you forward instead of backwards. Can be very useful on certain encounters with heavy movement.
  • ‍Time is Money     -- Goblin
    • Increases your Haste by 1%.
  • ‍Gnome     and
    ‍Night Elf    , with the active abilities
    ‍Escape Artist     for
    ‍Gnome     to break roots and
    ‍Shadowmeld     for
    ‍Night Elf    , have proven useful in the past.
    • However, you already have access to the same capabilities as Marksmanship Hunter with
      ‍Disengage       breaking roots on use and
      ‍Feign Death       generally working on the same things as
      ‍Shadowmeld       does, so they are much less useful for you.

Recommendation

For you as a Marksmanship Hunter, the overall most useful races for you to play would be

‍Dwarf for Alliance and
‍Tauren for Horde, with the former winning out overall since
‍Stoneform has had much more usefulness in Mythic+ compared to most other racial active abilities that don't effect your damage.

Cursor Macros

@Cursor Macros simply uses whichever ability you combined it with directly where you have your cursor without the usual second click confirmation. Can take some getting used to if you've never used it but makes all abilities like this faster to throw out.

@Cursor

‍Volley 

#showtooltip
/cast [@cursor] Volley

#showtooltip

‍Rapid Fire is channeling. This enables you to spam your next button while
‍Rapid Fire is still channeling without losing out on any damage by interrupting the cast too early.

Addons

    • WeakAuras is a powerful and flexible framework that allows the display of highly customizable graphics on World of Warcraft's user interface to indicate buffs, debuffs, and other relevant information. This addon was created to be a lightweight replacement for Power Auras but has since introduced more functionalities while remaining efficient and easy to use.
  • Plater -- Advanced Nameplates
    • Plater is a nameplate addon with an extraordinary amount of settings, out of the box debuff tracking, threat coloring, and support for scripting similar to WeakAuras and wago.io + the WeakAuras-Companion for Mod/Script/Profile updates.
  • Details -- In-depth Damage Meter
    • Most powerful, reliable and handsome damage meter.

Changes this Patch

Patch 11.0.7 - The War Within
Marksmanship Hunter

Patch 11.0.7

Marksmanship Changes

  • Trick Shots damage percentage increased to 75% (was 65%).
  • Razor Fragments AOE damage percentage increased to 35% (was 25%).
  • Dark Ranger: Black Arrow damage increased by 15%.
  • Dark Ranger: Shadow Surge damage increased by 25%.
  • Dark Ranger: Bleak Powder damage increased by 65%.

Patch 11.0.5

Hunter Changes

  • New Talent: Deathblow – Kill Command/Aimed Shot has a 10% chance to grant Deathblow. Deathblow: The cooldown of Kill Shot is reset. Your next Kill Shot can be used on any target, regardless of their current health.
    • Developer's note: Each Hunter specialization has a way to generate Deathblow, but only Marksmanship referred to it as Deathblow. These changes are meant to unify the Deathblow design while still allowing each specialization to interface with it in a unique way.
  • Steady Shot now generates 10 Focus baseline for all specs.
  • Tranquilizing Shots empowered by Kodo Tranquilizer will now prioritize players.
  • Updated animations for Volley and Rapid Fire.
  • Improved Kill Shot has been removed.
  • Hero Talents
    • Dark Ranger
      • New Talent: Bleak Arrows – Your auto shot now deals Shadow damage. Your auto shot has a 20%/8% chance to grant Deathblow.
      • New Talent: Phantom Pain – When Kill Command/Aimed Shot damages a target affected by Black Arrow, 8% of the damage dealt is replicated to each other unit affected by Black Arrow.
      • New Talent: Banshee’s Mark – Murder of Crows now deals Shadow damage and casting Black Arrow has a 25% chance to summon a Murder of Crows on your target.
      • New Talent: The Bell Tolls – Black Arrow is now usable on enemies with greater than 80% or less than 20% health.
      • New Talent: Shadow Dagger – While in combat,casting Disengage releases a fan of daggers at nearby enemies, dealing very low Shadow damage and slowing affected targets by 30%.
      • New Talent: Bleak Powder – Casting Black Arrow while Beast Cleave/Trick Shots is active causes Black Arrow to explode upon hitting a target, dealing moderate damage to nearby enemies.
      • New Talent: Soul Drinker – When an enemy affected by Black Arrow dies, you have a 10% chance to gain Deathblow.
      • Black Arrow has been redesigned – Kill Shot is now replaced with Black Arrow. Black Arrow: You attempt to finish off a wounded target, dealing high Shadow damage and low Shadow damage over time for 10 seconds. Only usable on enemies with less than 20% health.
      • Withering Fire has been redesigned – Every 3 casts of Bestial Wrath/While Trueshot is active, you surrender to darkness for 12 seconds. When you gain Deathblow, and Black Arrow automatically fires at your target and two additional Black Arrows at 50% effectiveness.
      • Shadow Surge has been redesigned – Periodic damage from Black Arrow has a small chance to erupt in a burst of darkness, dealing moderate Shadow damage to all enemies near the target. Damage reduced beyond 8 targets.
      • Visual effects updated for Shadow Surge, Bleak Powder, Withering Fire, and Black Arrow.
      • The following talents have been removed:
        • Dark Empowerment
        • Darkness Calls
        • Death Shade
        • Grave Reaper
        • Overshadow
        • Shadow Erasure
        • Shadow Lash
    • Sentinel
      • Lunar Storm’s visual effects have been updated.

Marksmanship Changes

  • New Talent: Pin Cushion – Casting Steady Shot reduces the cooldown of Aimed Shot by 2 seconds. Choice node with Improved Steady Shot.
  • New Talent: Improved Deathblow – Aimed Shot now has a 15% chance and Rapid Fire now has a 25% chance to grant Deathblow. Kill Shot’s critical strike damage is increased by 25%.
  • Improved Steady Shot has been updated – Now makes Steady Shot grant an additional 10 Focus.
  • Precise Shots renamed to Precise Shot and has been updated – Now empowers your next cast of Arcane Shot, Chimera Shot, or Multi-Shot to deal 100% increased damage (was 2 casts at 70% bonus).
  • Steady Focus has been updated – Casting Steady Shot increases your Haste by 8% for 15 seconds (was casting Steady Shot twice in a row).
  • Steady Focus no longer plays its visual effects when it is refreshed.
  • Trueshot now reduces the focus cost of Aimed Shot baseline.
  • Rapid Fire Barrage Rapid Fire effectiveness increased to 40% (was 30%).
  • Razor Fragments is now a rolling periodic.
  • Master Marksman now benefits from Unnatural Causes.
  • Wailing Arrow no longer consumes Trick Shots.
  • Fixed an issue that prevented Wailing Arrow from benefitting from Hydra’s Bite.
  • Nerub-ar Palace 4-set bonus updated – Consuming Precise Shots increases the damage of your next Aimed Shot by 20% (was 10%).
  • Nerub-ar Palace 4-set bonus no longer stacks (used to stack 2 times).
  • Nerub-ar Palace 4-set bonus will no longer be inconsistently consumed by Trick Shots-empowered Aimed Shots.
  • Nerub-ar Palace 4-set bonus will now consistently benefit all damage instances of a Trick Shots-empowered Aimed Shot.
  • Nerub-ar Palace 4-set bonus will now behave properly with spell-queued Arcane Shots and Multi-Shots.
  • The position of Unerring Vision and Calling the Shots has swapped.
  • Eagletalon’s True Focus has been removed.
  • Developers’ notes: Dark Ranger is overperforming in single target and we’re looking to reduce it while compensating with some AOE buffs to keep the AOE performance roughly the same.
  • Dark Ranger: Black Arrow damage reduced by 10%.
  • Dark Ranger: Bleak Powder damage increased by 25%.
  • Dark Ranger: Shadow Surge damage increased by 25%.
  • Developers’ notes: Symphonic Arsenal lost more bite than intended from the removal of Eagletalon’s True Focus.
  • Sentinel: Symphonic Arsenal damage increased by 15%.

Patch 11.0.2

Hunter Changes

  • ‍Rejuvenating Wind     now heals 12% maximum health over its duration (was 20%).
  • An issue with
    ‍Ghillie Suit     not activating when uncovered by
    ‍Flare     effect has been resolved.

Marksmanship Changes

  • ‍Wind Arrows     now fire after you cast
    ‍Aimed Shot    , rather than during their cast.
  • Many issues with
    ‍Wind Arrows     failing to fire or breaking have been resolved.
  • ‍Rapid Fire's     cooldown between procs of
    ‍Wind Arrows     has been reduced to 0.2 seconds (was 0.7 seconds).

Patch 11.0

Hunter Changes

  • All talent trees have had many talents move locations or have had their pathing updated.
  • New Talent:
    ‍Padded Armor     –
    ‍Survival of the Fittest     gains an additional charge.
  • New Talent:
    ‍Kodo Tranquilizer     –
    ‍Tranquilizing Shot     removes up to 1 additional Magic effect from its target.
  • New Talent:
    ‍Devilsaur Tranquilizer     – If
    ‍Tranquilizing Shot     removes only an Enrage effect, its cooldown is reduced by 5 seconds.
  • New Talent:
    ‍Scout's Instincts     – You cannot be slowed below 80% of your normal movement speed while
    ‍Aspect of the Cheetah     is active.
  • New Talent:
    ‍Scrappy     – Casting
    ‍Aimed Shot     reduces the cooldown of
    ‍Intimidation     and
    ‍Binding Shot     by 0.5 seconds.
  • New Talent:
    ‍Kindling Flare     – Stealthed enemies revealed by
    ‍Flare     remain revealed for 3 seconds after exiting the flare.
  • New Talent:
    ‍Unnatural Causes     – Your damage over time effects deal 10% increased damage. This effect is increased by 50% on targets below 20% health.
  • New Talent:
    ‍Moment of Opportunity     – When a trap triggers, you gain
    ‍Aspect of the Cheetah     for 3 seconds. Can only occur every 1 minute.
  • New Talent:
    ‍No Hard Feelings     – When
    ‍Misdirection     targets your pet, it reduces the damage they take by 50% for 5 seconds.
  • New Talent:
    ‍Territorial Instincts     – Casting
    ‍Intimidation     without an active pet summons one from your stable. Intimidation's cooldown is reduced by 5 sec.
  • New Talent:
    ‍Tar-Coated Bindings     –
    ‍Binding Shot     root duration is increased by 1 second.
  • New Talent:
    ‍Serrated Tips     – You gain 5% more     critical strike from critical strike sources.
  • New Talent:
    ‍Ghillie Suit     – You take 20% reduced damage while in
    ‍Camouflage    . This bonus persists 3 seconds after leaving Camouflage.
  • New Talent:
    ‍Specialized Arsenal     –
    ‍Aimed Shot     damage increased by 10%.
  • New Talent:
    ‍Blackrock Munitions     – The damage of
    ‍Explosive Shot     is increased by 8%.
  • New Talent:
    ‍Implosive Trap     – Hurls a fire trap to the target location that explodes when an enemy approaches, causing Fire damage and knocking all enemies up. Limit 1. Choice node with
    ‍High Explosive Trap    .
  • ‍Lone Survivor     now also reduces
    ‍Counter Shot     and
    ‍Muzzle     cooldown by 2 seconds.
  • ‍Survival of the Fittest     now reduces all damage you and your pet take by 30% (was 20%).
  • ‍Disruptive Rounds     now also grants 10 Focus when you interrupt an effect with
    ‍Counter Shot     or
    ‍Muzzle    .
  • ‍Quick Load     now resets the cooldown of
    ‍Scatter Shot     and
    ‍Bursting Shot    .
  • ‍Born To Be Wild     now reduces
    ‍Aspect of the Cheetah    ,
    ‍Survival of the Fittest    , and
    ‍Aspect of the Turtle     by 30 seconds (was 7/15%).
  • ‍Steady Shot     cast time reduced to 1.65 seconds (was 1.75 seconds).
  • ‍Explosive Shot     now explodes early when applied to a target that already is affected by Explosive Shot.
  • ‍Explosive Shot     projectile and explosion visual effects have been updated.
  • ‍Barrage    ,
    ‍Master Marksman    , and
    ‍Hydra's Bite     have moved to the Marksmanship talent tree.
  • ‍Bursting Shot     is now a choice node with
    ‍Scatter Shot     (was in Marksmanship tree).
  • The following talents are now 1 point:
    • ‍Improved Traps
    • ‍Pathfinding
    • ‍Trailblazer
    • ‍Wilderness Medicine
    • ‍Natural Mending
    • ‍Rejuvenating Wind
  • The following talents have been removed:
    • ‍Sentinel Owl
    • ‍Sentinel's Perception
    • ‍Sentinel's Protection
    • ‍Serpent Sting
    • ‍Poison Injection
    • ‍Stampede
    • ‍Beast Master
    • ‍Arctic Bola
    • ‍Nature's Endurance
    • ‍Serrated Shots
    • ‍Steel Trap
    • ‍Death Chakram

Marksmanship Changes

  • New Talent:
    ‍Rapid Fire Barrage     – Your
    ‍Barrage     now instead shoots
    ‍Rapid Fire     at up to five nearby enemies at 30% effectiveness but has its cooldown increased to 60 seconds.
  • New Talent:
    ‍Small Game Hunter     – The damage of
    ‍Multi-Shot     is increased by 75% and the damage of
    ‍Explosive Shot     is increased by 25%.
  • New Talent:
    ‍Penetrating Shots     – Gain     critical strike damage equal to 40% of your critical strike chance.
  • New Talent:
    ‍Kill Zone     – Your spells and attacks deal 8% more damage and ignore line of sight against any target in your
    ‍Volley    .
  • ‍Eagletalon's True Focus     has been redesigned –
    ‍Trueshot     lasts an additional 3 seconds. During Trueshot,
    ‍Aimed Shot     Focus cost is reduced by 50% and
    ‍Arcane Shot     and
    ‍Multi-Shot     casts an additional time at 30% effectiveness.
  • ‍Hydra's Bite     has been redesigned – When Aimed Shot strikes an enemy affected with your Serpent Sting, it spreads Serpent Sting to up to 2 nearby enemies. Serpent Sting's damage over time is increased by 20%.
  • ‍Killer Accuracy     has been updated –
    ‍Kill Shot         critical strike chance and critical strike damage are increased by 20%.
  • ‍Razor Fragments     has been updated –
    ‍Kill Shot     damage increase to 75% (was 50%). Moved to Gate 3.
  • ‍Legacy of the Windrunners     has been redesigned – Each time Rapid Fire deals damage, there is a 5% chance to coalesce a Wind Arrow at your target.
  • Wind Arrows damage increased by 300%. Wind Arrows are longer affected by Aimed Shot modifiers. No longer grants Focus or Aimed Shot charges after firing 24 Wind Arrows.
  • Wailing Arrow has been redesigned and is now passive – Now replaces your Aimed Shot with a Wailing Arrow after generating 20 Wind Arrows.
  • ‍Wailing Arrow     only silences the primary target and it now benefits from bonuses to
    ‍Aimed Shot     such as
    ‍Trick Shots    .
  • ‍Readiness     now causes
    ‍Trueshot     to immediately grant you
    ‍Wailing Arrow     and you generate 2 additional Wind Arrows while in
    ‍Trueshot    .
    ‍Wailing Arrow     resets the cooldown of
    ‍Rapid Fire     and generates 2 charges of
    ‍Aimed Shot    .
  • ‍Barrage    ,
    ‍Master Marksman    , and
    ‍Hydra's Bite     are now Marksmanship talents (was Class).
  • ‍Lone Wolf     reduced to 5% increased damage when you do not have an active pet (was 10%).
  • ‍Rapid Fire     damage increased by 2%.
  • ‍Arcane Shot     damage increased by 13%.
  • ‍Aimed Shot     damage increased by 10%.
  • ‍Trick Shots     ricochet damage reduced to 65% (was 70%).
  • ‍Precise Shots     now always grants 2 stacks and reduces the Focus cost of your next
    ‍Multi-Shot     or
    ‍Arcane Shot     by 50%.
  • ‍Multi-Shot     Focus cost increased to 30 (was 20).
  • Many 2-point talents are now 1 point.
  • ‍Bursting Shot     has moved to the Class tree.

FAQ

Patch 11.0.7 - The War Within
Marksmanship Hunter

Q: When do I use a Pet as a Marksmanship Hunter?

A: In almost all cases you won't, but you can quickly summon a Pet with

‍Primal Rage to provide
‍Bloodlust for your group if no one else has it.
